{Winner's luck?! Whichever side you are on, luck or no luck, one thing is clear
to me: these top players are too objective. They immediately tell you: I was
worse here, I was better there, with no euphoric or depressing feelings
clouding their judgement. Respect.} 43... a6 {Following the rule of thumbs in
the endgame: the side which is defending should search for simplifications,
exchanging the remaining pawns and liquidating into an easier position to
protect. Not this time.} ({The more active defense was:} 43... Kd4 44. Rd3+
Kxc4 45. f4 {and looks like the black rook is stranded on a4} gxf4 46. gxf4 b5
47. f5 Ra6 {not for long! A draw is now the most likely result.}) 44. Kd3 Kf5
